be the proper objects of Love. And herein is that partly verified, that Love is strong as Death. For as that grave which buries a dead man, doth likewise burie all his enemies (it being unnaturall to hate the dead, whom wee cannot hurt: for the utmost harme, that malice can doe, is to kill. And therefore it is noted as a prodigious hatred betweene the two emulous brothers of Thebes, Aetcocles and Polynices;

